\section{Quinn, 2001\hfill{}\textsc{CA}}
\label{sec-19}
\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{Listening to similarity relations}
\item What constitutes a good similarity measure?
\begin{enumerate}
\item The ways in which we are accustomed to talking about similarity relations are not as productive as they seem to be, and there are better ways to do it.
\item Comparison of various similarity relations from such a different point of view shows that they are more related to each other, and to a lot of other theory, than they appear to be in traditional modes of discourse.
\end{enumerate}
